
MERGING !!

Branching makes it easy to work within self-contained contexts. If we want to incorporate changes from one branch to another, we can use merge command. 
It basically means combining the changes from one branch to another. 

  * We always merge to the current HEAD Branch. 
  * We merge branches, bot committs. 

> STEPS TO MERGE -
-- a) Switch to or checkout the branch you want to merge the changes into (receiving branch).
   b) use the git merge command to merge changes from a specific branch into the current branch.

> COMMANDS -
  a> To show branches as well as commits 
 -- [git branch -v] 
  b> To merge     
     (First, we need to switch to the branch in which we want to merge or add the changes. then execute the command)
  -- [git merge <branch-name> ] 
  c> To create a merge commit 
  -- [git merge --no-ff ] -> It will always create a merge commit.
  d> To combine changes into a single commit 
  -- [git merge --squash ] 
  e> To abort a merge in progress 
  -- [git merge --abort] 






